; body-link-graph.fk — the body's link fabric as a computed graph: every .md
; page as a source of claims, and the concept tissue checked for ORPHANS —
; pages nothing points at.
;
; Born 2026-07-16 from a comparison Urs asked for: Wes Roth's "Claude Built
; the Ultimate Second Brain" (2026-07-14) and the natural20.com guide it
; points at name a lint that finds "orphan pages" — pages with no links
; pointing in. This body's lint (observe/door-link-health.fk) could not: its
; own header named the floor — "Nested doors (a receipt linking a receipt)
; need dir-relative path joining" — and so it saw only the 12-door ring.
; This cell closes that named floor (ingest/name-build-observe.fk: a named gap
; is a work order, not a shelf) and, with it, does the guide's orphan check —
; but as a NUMBER a fresh kernel recomputes, not as an LLM's opinion of its
; own vault.
;
; WHAT IS DIFFERENT FROM THE GUIDE (the honest "more"): their lint is a prompt
; — "ask Claude to audit the wiki" — so the auditor is the same mind that
; wrote the pages, and its verdict is unverifiable and unrepeatable. This is
; an organ: it returns a folded integer, it can FAIL (a planted orphan moves
; the count), and any witness recomputes it. The rule cannot drift from the
; practice because the rule IS the practice.
;
; SCOPE, chosen on principle rather than convenience — orphanhood means
; different things to different tissues:
;   SOURCES    — every .md in the body. Anything may point at anything; a
;                receipt citing a teaching genuinely un-orphans it.
;   CANDIDATES — the concept tissue only: teachings/ and docs/. NOT the door
;                ring (doors are the graph's ROOTS by definition — you arrive
;                at README; nothing must point at it), and NOT receipts/ (the
;                body's ontogeny, corpus row 733: a chronological witness
;                record nobody cites is normal, not a defect. Calling 592
;                receipts "orphans" would be a metric lying about a healthy
;                tissue).
;
; Composes, never copies (the one-home-per-organ law): the skip rule and
; anchor strip have ONE home in door-link-health.fk (dlh-skip? /
; dlh-strip-anchor) and are composed here. Named seam: the walk-for-"](" shape
; appears twice — dlh-scan COUNTS, blg-targets-loop COLLECTS. A later shell
; could express dlh-scan as a fold over the collection; dlh stays standalone
; today because it is witnessed, door-scoped, and re-witnessed by its own
; stamp. Named so it can be collected, not hidden.
;
; Known floor, inherited from door-link-health and confirmed by this cell's
; author the hour it was born: the scan is TEXTUAL — it counts "](" anywhere,
; including inside code fences and inside quoted prose. So quoting markdown
; link syntax MAKES a link: this cell's own receipt quoted a teaching's link
; verbatim and the count went 156 -> 157, the new claim being the literal
; "receipts/...". That is not purely a false positive — GitHub renders the
; quoted link as a live broken link too — but a fence-aware scan would be the
; more honest instrument. Named as a next shell, not fixed here.
;
; fkwu-carrier (host I/O: fs_list/fs_exists/read_file) — proven live by
; receipt, never claimed four-way. Run from the repo root.
;
; run:
;   cat form/form-stdlib/core.fk grammars/line-grammar.fk \
;       observe/door-link-health.fk observe/body-link-graph.fk > /tmp/blgbase.fk
;   ( cat /tmp/blgbase.fk; echo '(body-link-graph-check)' ) > /tmp/blg.fk
;   ./fkwu --src /tmp/blg.fk        ; -> 63 (self-check)
;   ( cat /tmp/blgbase.fk; echo '(blg-field-code)' ) > /tmp/blgf.fk
;   ./fkwu --src /tmp/blgf.fk       ; -> orphans*10^6 + broken*10^3 + candidates
;
; witnessed: 2026-07-16 -> self-check 63; 764 sources, 457 resolved
;   path-claims, 156 BROKEN, 31 candidates, 14 ORPHANS; field 14156031,
;   safe 1. Whole-body walk costs ~1.2s on fkwu.
;   Re-witnessed the same hour: field 13156031 -- THIRTEEN orphans. Writing
;   the comparison into SECOND-BRAIN.md cited lc-trust-over-fear.md, and the
;   citation un-orphaned it. The observation changed the observed: naming an
;   orphan is what ends its orphanhood. Both numbers are true of their
;   moment and both are kept, in the door-link-health discipline (keep the
;   miss and the heal); 14 is what the body was before it looked.
;   Falsified before believed: a planted link to an orphan moved the count
;   14 -> 13 and back. Three broken classes verified by hand against the
;   filesystem before the number was reported (a link resolving to
;   receipts/receipts/..., a concept page referenced 5x that exists nowhere,
;   and 44 claims on form/docs/ -- a tree that does not exist).
;   What the graph revealed that no reading had: 77 of 156 broken claims
;   point into docs/vision-kb/concepts/, which holds ONE file, and 44 into
;   form/docs/, which holds none. These are not rot; they are the SEAM OF THE
;   CURATION that made this repo public-able (MANIFEST.md's IN/OUT scope).
;   The pages that were OUT stayed out; the links to them were never
;   re-witnessed. Healing is deliberate work, NOT this organ's job: most of
;   the broken claims live in receipts/, and a receipt is an immutable
;   witness record -- silently rewriting 592 of them to make a number green
;   would forge the body's own ontogeny (corpus row 733).
;   receipts/2026-07-16-second-brain-compared-link-graph.md
;
;   CORRECTION 2026-07-16 (same night, kept in place per the discipline above
;   -- the miss and the heal). "Most of the broken claims live in receipts/"
;   was ASSERTED, never counted, and it is false: FOUR of 156 live in
;   receipts/ (2.6%). 90 are in form/, 35 in teachings/, 27 in docs/ -- all
;   freely healable tissue. The immutability law is real and still holds; its
;   SCOPE was assumed, and the assumption made a deferral look like reverence
;   while 152 healable claims sat. The grep that falsifies it takes one second
;   and this cell already had every function needed to run it. Corpus row 735
;   (scrupulosity) is the word for what happened. Healed the same night by
;   observe/heal-curation-seam.fk, which composes THIS cell's blg-lands? as
;   its decision: 108 claims healed across 29 files, receipts/ touched 0 (it
;   refuses them by construction), self-check unmoved at 63 -- the instrument
;   was not softened to move its own number. Field 13156031 -> 7041032.
;   Still standing and named as work, not shelf: 10 claims whose target is an
;   existing DIRECTORY (this cell calls them broken; GitHub renders them
;   live -- an instrument floor, deliberately not "fixed" by the agent whose
;   own number it would improve), the 4 receipts/ claims (law), and 27
;   non-concept claims on OUT tissue (.py carriers, kernels/*.md) that need
;   per-case judgement rather than one rule.
;   receipts/2026-07-16-curation-seam-healed.md
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk grammars/line-grammar.fk observe/door-link-health.fk

(do
    ; ── path algebra: resolve a link against the dir of the file holding it ─
    (defn blg-rev-loop (l acc) (if (eq (len l) 0) acc (blg-rev-loop (tail l) (cons (head l) acc))))
    (defn blg-rev (l) (blg-rev-loop l (list)))
    (defn blg-joinsegs (l acc)
        (if (eq (len l) 0) acc
            (blg-joinsegs (tail l)
                (if (str_eq acc "") (head l) (str_concat acc (str_concat "/" (head l)))))))
    ; acc is a REVERSED stack, so ".." is exactly (tail acc) — pop the last
    ; segment. "." and "" (from "a//b" or a trailing slash) are no-ops. A ".."
    ; past the root clamps at the root rather than escaping it.
    (defn blg-norm-loop (segs acc)
        (if (eq (len segs) 0) acc
            (do
                (let s (head segs))
                (blg-norm-loop (tail segs)
                    (if (str_eq s "..")
                        (if (eq (len acc) 0) acc (tail acc))
                        (if (str_eq s ".") acc
                            (if (str_eq s "") acc (cons s acc))))))))
    (defn blg-norm (p) (blg-joinsegs (blg-rev (blg-norm-loop (split-on p "/") (list))) ""))
    (defn blg-lastslash (p from best)
        (do
            (let i (find-from p "/" from))
            (if (lt i 0) best (blg-lastslash p (add i 1) i))))
    (defn blg-dirname (p)
        (do
            (let i (blg-lastslash p 0 -1))
            (if (lt i 0) "" (substring p 0 i))))
    (defn blg-resolve (fromfile target)
        (do
            (let d (blg-dirname fromfile))
            (blg-norm (if (str_eq d "") target (str_concat d (str_concat "/" target))))))

    ; ── file walk (recursive; hidden dirs are not the body) ────────────────
    (defn blg-ends-with? (s suf)
        (if (lt (str_len s) (str_len suf)) 0
            (if (str_eq (substring s (sub (str_len s) (str_len suf)) (str_len s)) suf) 1 0)))
    ; a name is a directory when it lists children — fs_list on a file is
    ; empty (probed live 2026-07-16: file -> 0, dir -> 12). An empty dir reads
    ; as a file and contributes nothing either way.
    (defn blg-dir? (p) (if (gt (len (fs_list p)) 0) 1 0))
    (defn blg-hidden? (nm) (if (str_eq (substring nm 0 1) ".") 1 0))
    (defn blg-append (a b) (if (eq (len a) 0) b (cons (head a) (blg-append (tail a) b))))
    (defn blg-collect-loop (dir names acc)
        (if (eq (len names) 0) acc
            (do
                (let nm (head names))
                (let p (if (str_eq dir "") nm (str_concat dir (str_concat "/" nm))))
                (blg-collect-loop dir (tail names)
                    (if (eq (blg-hidden? nm) 1) acc
                        (if (eq (blg-dir? p) 1)
                            (blg-append acc (blg-collect p))
                            (if (eq (blg-ends-with? nm ".md") 1) (cons p acc) acc)))))))
    (defn blg-collect (dir) (blg-collect-loop dir (fs_list dir) (list)))

    ; ── the graph's edges: resolved link targets held by one file ──────────
    ; composes dlh's DECISIONS (skip rule, anchor strip); collects where
    ; dlh-scan counts.
    (defn blg-targets-loop (path text from acc)
        (do
            (let i (find-from text "](" from))
            (if (lt i 0) acc
                (do
                    (let s (add i 2))
                    (let j (find-from text ")" s))
                    (if (lt j 0) acc
                        (do
                            (let t (substring text s j))
                            (blg-targets-loop path text (add j 1)
                                (if (eq (dlh-skip? t) 1) acc
                                    (cons (blg-resolve path (dlh-strip-anchor t)) acc)))))))))
    (defn blg-targets (path) (blg-targets-loop path (read_file path) 0 (list)))
    (defn blg-all-targets (paths acc)
        (if (eq (len paths) 0) acc
            (blg-all-targets (tail paths) (blg-append (blg-targets (head paths)) acc))))

    ; ── the two health reads ───────────────────────────────────────────────
    ; a path-claim lands when a cell answers there. read_file on a directory
    ; answers "" (the lesson door-link-health taught its own author), so a
    ; directory target is a broken claim, exactly as in the door ring.
    (defn blg-lands? (p) (if (gt (str_len (read_file p)) 0) 1 0))
    (defn blg-count-broken (ts n)
        (if (eq (len ts) 0) n
            (blg-count-broken (tail ts) (add n (sub 1 (blg-lands? (head ts)))))))
    (defn blg-member? (x l)
        (if (eq (len l) 0) 0
            (if (str_eq x (head l)) 1 (blg-member? x (tail l)))))
    (defn blg-count-orphans (cands ts n)
        (if (eq (len cands) 0) n
            (blg-count-orphans (tail cands) ts
                (add n (sub 1 (blg-member? (head cands) ts))))))

    ; ── the scoped reads (see SCOPE in the header) ─────────────────────────
    ; the repo root lists as "." — fs_list "" answers nothing (probed live
    ; 2026-07-16: "" -> 0, "." -> 47). Source paths therefore carry a "./"
    ; head, which blg-norm dissolves ("." is a no-op segment), so a resolved
    ; target from "./README.md" and a candidate path from blg-collect
    ; "teachings" meet in the same normalized form — which is what makes the
    ; membership test below mean anything.
    (defn blg-sources () (blg-collect "."))
    (defn blg-candidates () (blg-append (blg-collect "teachings") (blg-collect "docs")))
    (defn blg-orphans () (blg-count-orphans (blg-candidates) (blg-all-targets (blg-sources) (list)) 0))
    (defn blg-broken () (blg-count-broken (blg-all-targets (blg-sources) (list)) 0))

    ; ── the folded scalar witness (the hdc-field-code discipline) ──────────
    ;   field = orphans*10^6 + broken*10^3 + candidates
    ; injective while broken<=999 and candidates<=999 — guarded, so the band
    ; cannot stay green after a digit slot stops being true.
    (defn blg-field-code-safe-for (broken cands)
        (if (lt broken 1000) (if (lt cands 1000) 1 0) 0))
    (defn blg-field-code-safe? ()
        (blg-field-code-safe-for (blg-broken) (len (blg-candidates))))
    (defn blg-field-code ()
        (do
            (let ts (blg-all-targets (blg-sources) (list)))
            (add (mul (blg-count-orphans (blg-candidates) ts 0) 1000000)
            (add (mul (blg-count-broken ts 0) 1000)
                 (len (blg-candidates))))))

    ; ── self-check: the path algebra on synthetic truth (pure), then live ──
    (defn blgk (ok bit) (if ok bit 0))
    (defn body-link-graph-check ()
        (add (blgk (str_eq (blg-resolve "receipts/x.md" "../observe/a.fk") "observe/a.fk") 1)
        (add (blgk (str_eq (blg-resolve "README.md" "SECOND-BRAIN.md") "SECOND-BRAIN.md") 2)
        (add (blgk (str_eq (blg-resolve "teachings/concepts/c.md" "../../axioms/a.form") "axioms/a.form") 4)
        (add (blgk (str_eq (blg-resolve "docs/vision-kb/x.md" "./y.md") "docs/vision-kb/y.md") 8)
        (add (blgk (eq (blg-member? "b" (list "a" "b")) 1) 16)
             (blgk (gt (len (blg-candidates)) 20) 32)))))))
    0)
